TextBody:
Stephen,

Could we get the following form the Proxy Servers?
Best if pasted into the edit window in an ADMIN PowerShell ISE session. Then Copy the text from the output window.

Clear-Host
$Servers = "CHN-SHG-NW-PRXY","NLD-AMF-NW-PRXY","USA-RNC-NW-PRXY","SGP-SGP-NW-PRXY"

Foreach ($Server in $Servers){ 
"**** Checking Host $Server ****"
Invoke-Command -ComputerName $Server { 
$README_paths = gci "C:Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITFSAA*README.txt" -Recurse
"**** README_paths ****
$README_paths "
Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_Service -PipelineVariable Service  |Where-Object {($_.DisplayName -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.DisplayName -like "Netwrix*")}|
ForEach-Object {
    Get-Process -Id $_.ProcessId |
    Select-Object -Property @{label='Status';expression={$Service.State}},
                            @{label='DisplayName';expression={$Service.DisplayName}},
                            @{label='Log-on-AS';expression={$Service.StartName}},
                            @{label='Start_Up_Mode';expression={$Service.StartMode}},
                            StartTime
                            } |Sort-Object |Format-Table  Status, Start_Up_Mode, Name, StartTime, Log-on-AS -AutoSize 
                }
} 


If it is truly missing on any of the host we can pull it from NEA server path and place it where it is needed on the proxy host.
%sainstalldir%FSAASensitiveDatajdk-17.0.7+7-jreconfsecuritypolicy

Let's then run the jobs again to see if there same file is noted in the error.

Again, thank You for your time.

Stephen,

Thank You for the update.
 
Looks like we did not have rights to the needed folder path.

Let try this script
Clear-Host
$domain = "$env:USERDOMAIN"
$Cred = Get-Credential "$domainDomain_Admin_Account"
$Servers = "CHN-SHG-NW-PRXY","NLD-AMF-NW-PRXY","USA-RNC-NW-PRXY","SGP-SGP-NW-PRXY" 

Foreach ($Server in $Servers){
"**** Checking Host $Server ****"
Invoke-Command -ComputerName $Server -Credential $Cred {
$README_paths = gci "D:Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITFSAA*README.txt" -Recurse
"**** README_paths ****
$README_paths "
Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_Service -PipelineVariable Service  |Where-Object {($_.DisplayName -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.DisplayName -like "Netwrix*")}|
ForEach-Object {
    Get-Process -Id $_.ProcessId |
    Select-Object -Property @{label='Status';expression={$Service.State}},
                            @{label='DisplayName';expression={$Service.DisplayName}},
                            @{label='Log-on-AS';expression={$Service.StartName}},
                            @{label='Start_Up_Mode';expression={$Service.StartMode}},
                            StartTime
                            } |Sort-Object |Format-Table  Status, Start_Up_Mode, DisplayName, StartTime, Log-on-AS -AutoSize
                }
}

Let try this script
Clear-Host
$domain = "$env:USERDOMAIN"

Foreach ($Server in $Servers){
"**** Checking Host $Server ****"
Invoke-Command -ComputerName $Server -Credential $Cred {
$README_paths = gci "D:Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITFSAA*README.txt" -Recurse
"**** README_paths ****
$README_paths "
Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_Service -PipelineVariable Service  |Where-Object {($_.DisplayName -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.DisplayName -like "Netwrix*")}|
ForEach-Object {
    Get-Process -Id $_.ProcessId |
    Select-Object -Property @{label='Status';expression={$Service.State} },
                            @{label='DisplayName';expression={$Service.DisplayName} },
                            @{label='Log-on-AS';expression={$Service.StartName} },
                            @{label='Start_Up_Mode';expression={$Service.StartMode} },
                            StartTime
                            } |Sort-Object |Format-Table  Status, Start_Up_Mode, DisplayName, StartTime, Log-on-AS -AutoSize
                }
}

Clear-Host

Foreach ($Server in $Servers){

$README_paths = gci "D:Program Files (x86)STEALTHbitsStealthAUDITFSAA*README.txt" -Recurse
"**** README_paths ****
$README_paths "
Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_Service -PipelineVariable Service  |Where-Object {($_.DisplayName -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.DisplayName -like "Netwrix*")}|
ForEach-Object {
    Get-Process -Id $_.ProcessId |
    Select-Object -Property @{label='Status';expression={$Service.State} },
                            @{label='DisplayName';expression={$Service.DisplayName} },
                            @{label='Log-on-AS';expression={$Service.StartName} },
                            @{label='Start_Up_Mode';expression={$Service.StartMode} },
                            StartTime
                            } |Sort-Object |Format-Table  Status, Start_Up_Mode, DisplayName, StartTime, Log-on-AS -AutoSize
                }
}
